_______________________________________________________________
Delete local Git configuration (within a repository):
git config user.name
git config user.email
    rm .git/config
_______________________________________________________________
Delete global Git configuration (typically located in your home directory):
git config --global user.name
git config --global user.email
    rm ~/.gitconfig
_______________________________________________________________
cd path/to/your/project 
git init 
_______________________________________________________________
git remote add origin https://github.com/your-username/your-repo-name.git 
git add . 
git commit -m "Initial commit" 
_______________________________________________________________
git push -u origin main 
or 
git push -u origin main --force 
_______________________________________________________________
Rename Your Branch (if necessary) : 
git branch -m master main
_______________________________________________________________
Pull from a Specific Remote (To copy from remote repo)
git pull origin

Pull from a Specific Branch:
git pull origin main   (git pull <remote-name> <branch-name>)

OR JUST,  git pull   ,to simply copy updated from repo
_______________________________________________________________
Delete local Git configuration (within a repository):
rm .git/config
_______________________________________________________________
Delete global Git configuration (typically located in your home directory):
rm ~/.gitconfig
_______________________________________________________________
